    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1876-03-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1876-03-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="115" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d115">
                <head>No. 105.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">General <persName type="from">Schenck</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Fish</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1876-03-02">
                            <hi rend="italic">March</hi> 2,
                                1876</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Lord Derby calls attention to third clause, subsection two, of
                            extradition act, and declines to give up Winslow unless promise is made
                            by law or by arrangement that he shall be tried only for the extradition
                            crime.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>SCHENCK.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
